content:
Intelligently invalidates Redis cache entries when model or data files are modified. Helps maintain cache consistency by clearing relevant keys based on the modified file patterns.

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "if [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *models/*.js ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *models/*.py ]]; then MODEL_NAME=$(basename \"${CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH%.*}\"); echo \"ðŸ”„ Invalidating Redis cache for model: $MODEL_NAME\" && redis-cli --scan --pattern \"*${MODEL_NAME}*\" | xargs -L 1 redis-cli DEL 2>/dev/null && redis-cli FLUSHDB ASYNC 2>/dev/null && echo 'âœ… Cache invalidated'; fi"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
